Please also see todo.txt

1. Use ct.sql to create database
2. Modify variable registry_path to set it to where you want
   the registry xml to be
3. Modify hosts.txt to add your own hosts

Registry is the code is writes/updates the registry xml, it 
freshes the stuff every 30 seconds

RegistryClient is just an example of how to get some info
from the registry.

In RegistryClient.java, modify variable reg_xml

cmd.sh is an example of compiling and running the stuff.  
This can be improved.